        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-02-04T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-02-04T19:00:00-05:00" n="382" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d382">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24532/1–3046: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Berle</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-02-04T19:00:00-05:00">February 4, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>176. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 207 Jan 30.<note n="15" xml:id="d382fn15">Not printed.</note> Dept is actively pursuing subject of
                    air base installations. Commitment to turn installations over to Brazilian Govt
                    now admitted by <gloss target="#t_FLC1">FLC</gloss> as well as War Dept but
                    channels and mechanics still to be worked out. Instructions will be sent as soon
                    as possible. Temporary delivery of custody suggested <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> undesirable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
